race.comment: NEW BUSINESS (3) ran a strong race last time out beaten only 1.1L over 1400m at Warwick Farm from the speed. Spiked his figures and the step up to the mile shouldn't bother. In a top barn and they've booked the in-form Boudvillain. Well placed holding the form. SOUTHERN SKY (8) needed the first-up outing at Kembla Grange and she's going to be sharper over a mile with the extra fitness. She's right up to this at best. SIMPLY NUTBUSH (4) won his Maiden here and then came back and just missed as favourite over this distance. Uses the low barrier and is a decent chance to bounce. WHACK ATTACK (5) led and won her Maiden here first up and then just missed a place at Goulburn over 1400m. She's sure to keep improving and may control the race. Guymer sticks with CALL ME SON (1), who can build on his first-up Maiden win here over 1400m.
